    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Geofroy</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 9, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of the 2d instant, relative to the case of one Cauvet, a
                    French subject, unlawfully enlisted into the military service of the United
                    States, and who, on the 23d of December last, was serving in the 3d regiment of
                    V. H. V., at Morris island. I now have the honor to inform you that the matter
                    has been referred to the proper department for investigation.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, the renewed assurance of my high consideration,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">L. de Geofray,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
